> This Rump Steak and Truffled Dauphinoise is a luxurious dinner night option, made with
> premium ingredients for a real taste of luxury at home!

Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Remove the @21 Day Aged British Rump Steaks{2} from your fridge to allow them to come
up to room temperature before cooking. Bring a large #saucepan{} of water with @salt{1/2%tsp}
to the boil for the potatoes.

Peel and slice the @potatoes{450%g} into 1cm thick rounds. Peel and grate the
@garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}). Trim the @green beans{150%g}.

Once boiling, add the potato slices to the water and simmer until just tender,
~{8-12%minutes}.

Once cooked, reserve some of the potato water, then carefully drain in a #colander{}.

When the potatoes have 5 mins left, heat a drizzle of oil in a medium saucepan on
medium heat.

Once hot, add half the garlic and cook until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}, then add the
@creme fraiche{150%g}, @chicken stock paste{10%g}, reserved potato water and half the
@grated hard Italian Style Cheese{10%g}.

Mix together, bring to the boil, then remove from the heat. Season to taste with
@salt{} and @ground black pepper{}.

Lay the cooked potato slices in layers in an appropriately sized #ovenproof dish{},
then pour over the creamy sauce.

Sprinkle the remaining @grated hard Italian Style Cheese{10%g} on top and bake on the
top shelf of your oven until golden brown and bubbly, ~{15-20%minutes}.

> TIP: Put the dish onto a baking tray to catch any drips.

Meanwhile, wash out the (now empty) medium saucepan. Pour in the @water{150%ml} for
the jus, then bring to the boil on high heat.

Stir in the @red wine jus paste{15%g}, then reduce the heat to medium. Allow the
sauce to bubble and thicken, stirring regularly, ~{5-6%minutes}. Set aside and cover
with a #lid{} or #foil{} to keep warm.

While the jus simmers, season the steaks with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}.

Heat a large #frying pan{} on high heat with a drizzle of oil.

> TIP: Rump steaks naturally vary in shape, so adjust the following timings depending
> on how you like yours cooked.

Once very hot, lay the steaks into the pan and fry until browned and medium-rare,
about ~{75%seconds} on each side.

> TIP: Lower the heat and cook each side for 1 min more if you like it more well done.

Once cooked, transfer to a #board{}, cover with foil and allow to rest for a couple
of mins.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. The steak is
> safe to eat when the outside is browned.

While the steaks rest, heat the (now empty) frying pan on medium-high heat with a
drizzle of oil if needed.

Once hot, add the green beans and stir-fry until starting to char, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir in the remaining @garlic clove{1}, then turn the heat down to medium and cook
for ~{1%minute}.

Add a splash of water and immediately cover with a lid or some foil. Cook until the
beans are tender, ~{4-5%minutes}, then from the heat.

When the dauphinoise is ready, remove from the oven and sprinkle over the @truffle zest{1}.

Slice your steaks widthways into 1cm slices and transfer to your plates. Spoon over
the red wine jus (reheat first if needed).

Serve with the truffled dauphinoise and garlicky green beans alongside.

Enjoy!